steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Allow the dough to rise for 1 hour (if bought the dough, let it rise in the bag)
- Dice the tomatoes
- Dice the onions

### Steps
1. Preheat oven to 400°F
2. Flour hands lightly and pat dough evenly into lightly greased or nonstick pizza pan (or turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and roll to desired thickness)
3. Shred chicken (white meat only; 2 cups)
4. Combine chicken, shredded Italian-blend cheese, and 1/4 cup dressing
5. Spread Alfredo evenly over crust, then top evenly with chicken mixture; bake 18–20 minutes (depending on thickness of pizza) or until thoroughly heated
6. Let stand 5 minutes
7. Chop salad greens and place in medium bowl; stir in tomatoes, onions, and remaining 1/4 cup dressing until blended
8. Top pizza with salad mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese
9. Slice and serve

#### Tips
- For a crispier crust, prebake dough 7–8 minutes. Add sauce and chicken mixture; bake 8–10 more minutes. Top with salad green mixture; slice and serve
